Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a new attention module for convolutional neural networks and evaluates its performance on image classification and object detection tasks. This is a core area of computer vision research.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new module that can be integrated into any CNN architecture and is end-to-end trainable. This falls under the domain of machine learning.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new attention mechanism that can adaptively refine features, which is a key aspect of artificial intelligence research.
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a new module that can be integrated into neural networks and improves their performance. This falls under the domain of neural computing.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper evaluates the proposed module on image classification and object detection tasks, which are multimedia applications.
